    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2003-09-25</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2003-12-04T18:38:47Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Amends Federal transportation law to expand the Federal flight deck officer program (providing for the arming of pilots of passenger aircraft) to include pilots of cargo aircraft.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>82</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2003-11-10</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Passed Senate without amendment</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2003-12-04T18:39:28Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>(This measure has not been amended since it was introduced. The summary has been expanded because action occurred on the measure.)</b></p> <p>Declares the sense of Congress that members of a flight deck crew of a cargo aircraft should be armed with a firearm and taser to defend the cargo aircraft against an attack by terrorists that could result in the aircraft's use as a weapon of mass destruction or for other terrorist purposes.</p> <p>Amends Federal transportation law to expand the Federal flight deck officer program (providing for the arming of pilots of passenger aircraft) to include pilots of cargo aircraft.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
